  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sri Arunodayam is a home in South India for abandoned children with intellectual disability (ID). It was founded in 2002 as a registered public charitable trust and recognized in 2008 as a Reception Unit by the State Government of Tamil Nadu. Sri Arunodayam is one among very few homes in India that actually look after children with intellectual disabilities. Most homes act as day care centers that are funded by parents.</narrative>
  </description>
